    <forecast>
        <area aac="SA_FA001" description="South Australia" type="region">
            <forecast-period start-time-local="2026-07-01T16:04:39+09:30" end-time-local="2026-07-01T16:04:39+09:30" start-time-utc="2026-07-01T06:34:39Z" end-time-utc="2026-07-01T06:34:39Z">
                <text type="warning_summary_footer">For latest warnings go to www.bom.gov.au, subscribe to RSS feeds, call 1300 659 210* or listen for warnings on relevant TV and radio broadcasts.</text>
                <text type="synoptic_situation">A series of low pressure systems passing over waters to the south will extend cold fronts that will cross over SA through to the end of the week. A high pressure system is then forecast to move into the Bight from late Friday and extend a ridge across the state over the weekend, as it slowly moves southeastwards towards Tasmania.</text>
                <text type="product_footer">* Calls to 1300 numbers cost around 27.5c incl. GST, higher from mobiles or public phones.</text>
            </forecast-period>
        </area>
        <area aac="SA_PW013" description="North West Pastoral" type="public-district" parent-aac="SA_FA001">
            <forecast-period index="0" start-time-local="2026-07-01T15:00:00+09:30" end-time-local="2026-07-02T00:00:00+09:30" start-time-utc="2026-07-01T05:30:00Z" end-time-utc="2026-07-01T14:30:00Z">
                <text type="forecast">Clear. Winds westerly 30 to 45 km/h decreasing to 25 to 35 km/h in the late afternoon then turning northwesterly 20 to 30 km/h in the evening.</text>
            </forecast-period>
            <forecast-period index="1" start-time-local="2026-07-02T00:00:00+09:30" end-time-local="2026-07-03T00:00:00+09:30" start-time-utc="2026-07-01T14:30:00Z" end-time-utc="2026-07-02T14:30:00Z">
                <text type="forecast">Partly cloudy. Medium chance of showers south of Woomera, most likely in the afternoon and evening. Near zero chance of rain elsewhere. Winds west to northwesterly 25 to 35 km/h tending west to southwesterly in the middle of the day then becoming light in the late evening. Overnight temperatures falling to between 5 and 8 with daytime temperatures reaching between 16 and 19.</text>
                <text type="uv_alert">Sun protection 11:20am to 1:50pm, UV Index predicted to reach 3 [Moderate]</text>
            </forecast-period>
            <forecast-period index="2" start-time-local="2026-07-03T00:00:00+09:30" end-time-local="2026-07-04T00:00:00+09:30" start-time-utc="2026-07-02T14:30:00Z" end-time-utc="2026-07-03T14:30:00Z">
                <text type="forecast">Partly cloudy. Slight chance of a shower south of Coober Pedy, near zero chance elsewhere. Light winds becoming west to southwesterly 15 to 20 km/h in the early morning then tending southeast to southwesterly in the middle of the day. Overnight temperatures falling to around 7 with daytime temperatures reaching between 15 and 18.</text>
            </forecast-period>
            <forecast-period index="3" start-time-local="2026-07-04T00:00:00+09:30" end-time-local="2026-07-05T00:00:00+09:30" start-time-utc="2026-07-03T14:30:00Z" end-time-utc="2026-07-04T14:30:00Z">
                <text type="forecast">Cloudy. The chance of morning fog south of Woomera. Slight chance of a shower north of Marla, most likely in the morning. Near zero chance of rain elsewhere. Light winds becoming east to southeasterly 15 to 25 km/h during the morning. Overnight temperatures falling to around 7 with daytime temperatures reaching around 16.</text>
            </forecast-period>
            <forecast-period index="4" start-time-local="2026-07-05T00:00:00+09:30" end-time-local="2026-07-06T00:00:00+09:30" start-time-utc="2026-07-04T14:30:00Z" end-time-utc="2026-07-05T14:30:00Z">
                <text type="forecast">Cloudy. Winds easterly 15 to 25 km/h. Overnight temperatures falling to around 7 with daytime temperatures reaching around 15.</text>
            </forecast-period>
        </area>
